                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d480</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">480</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-06-26T23:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-06-26T23:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-26T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-26T23:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-27T13:00:00+09:00">June 27, 1948—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 27—8:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1166. <hi rend="italic">Aide-mémoire</hi> containing text MFN treatment
                    (refDeptel 922, June 24) occupied areas corrected to conform Deptel 928, June
                    25, 8 p.m., presented Foreign Office July 27. Poker-face reception with reaction
                    to come which Embassy has every reason to believe will be as foreshadowed in
                    Embtel 1161, June 26, 6 p.m.</p>
                <p>Sent Department at 1166; repeated Shanghai 537.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
